Good Evening, Brunswick CSD Families:

This is a reminder that we will be holding a Virtual 6th Grade Orientation for Parents & Families TOMORROW, Wednesday, September 9, 2020, from 2:30-3:30 PM. The Google Meet link to join is: meet.google.com/skc-gwhg-xkh

If you have any questions, please reach out to building principal, Ken Rizzo, at krizzo@brunswickcsd.org. If you cannot attend the orientation, we will be recording and posting it to our district website under "News" shortly following the orientation.

We look forward to welcoming our newest middle school students and their families to a new year at Tamarac Secondary School!

Thank you!

Brunswick CSD

post_text:
REMINDER: Chromebook distribution is happening today until 6 PM.

PLEASE SEE THE UPDATED GUIDANCE BELOW REGARDING CHROMEBOOKS FROM OUR IT DEPARTMENT:

1) If your child is full-time K-6, you SHOULD NOT pick up a Chromebook
2) If your child is in a fully remote program K-12, you MAY pick up a Chromebook (but you do not NEED to if you have your own access to technology)
3) If your child is in the hybrid program 7-12, you MUST pick up a Chromebook (teachers may ask students to bring Chromebooks back and forth from home for continued instruction; the IT department kindly requests that students do not use their personal devices for the hybrid model)

Should you have any questions or concerns, please email Anthony Denovellis at adenovellis@brunswickcsd.org. Thank you!

post_text:
Dear parents,

On Monday, July 27th at 12 noon, I would like to host a Google Meet for all members of the elementary school community to address any questions or concerns that you may have about elementary instruction in September.

We still have much to learn about guidance from New York State and other agencies on reopening, but many district employees have been working hard to address whatever scenarios may be present when we begin school, and this will give us an opportunity to share what we have been working on - trust me, it is a lot!

Please use the link below to join the meeting. I‚Äôll do my best to share what I know so far, and to the find out answers to the questions that you may have. The link is https://meet.google.com/tfn-pwpv-jkc

If you would care to send me questions in advance, please send them to rpogue@brunswickcsd.org
I hope this meet will be informative and begin to address many questions that we face in these uncertain times.

Sincerely,

Rich Pogue
Principal, Tamarac Elementary School

post_text:
Rensselaer County is once again providing a free food program for those 18 and under through the summer! The Eastwick Press is happy to provide their building, the former Grafton Elementary School at the corner of NY Route 2 and Babcock Lake Road, in Grafton for the lunch and afternoon snack portion of the program.

This is available Monday through Friday, starting July 13. The hours for free lunch pick up are 11:30 arm to 12:30 pm, and between 1:30 to 2 pm for snacks. Snacks can also be picked up during the lunch hour.

No documentation or proof of residency is required. There will be a well marked drive up window, through which the food will be handed out. The number of lunches available will equal the amount of children in the household.

Please note that this is pick up only. Delivery is unavailable to communities because of health and insurance regulations.

post_text: Good Afternoon, Tamarac! Today, we‚Äôd like to take a moment to give a special shoutout to Michele Blake. As the President of the Tamarac Booster Club, Michele has been an extraordinary leader. She has created an inspiring vision for the future, motivated those around her to engage in that vision and delivered on the vision each and every day. She has truly gone above and beyond to support our student athletes and their families as well as the entire student body and our community. As you know, these are volunteer positions that require a significant amount of personal time to do the job and do it well. To highlight just a few of Michele‚Äôs accomplishments this year, she was instrumental in the Hall of Fame revitalization, launching the Bengal Bistro, recognition of our Athletes, Coaches, Officials and Administration, donations to the Back Pack Program and Food Pantry, coordination of the Coach Jones Tribute and organization of the Athletic Award Pick Up Day. Thank you for your continued commitment and dedication Michele. We appreciate you!

Dear parents of incoming Kindergarten students and prospective Pre-k students:

Senior Families: Please see the following message from senior advisors, Mr. Jacques and Mrs. Bishop:

The time has finally come, your caps and gowns have arrived!

Mr Jacques and I will be at school on Wednesday, June 17th, the same day you are scheduled to pick up the contents from your lockers, to hand out your caps and gowns. We will be stationed somewhere in front of the school.

If you have any questions or concerns, please email Mr Jacques or Mrs Bishop.

Reminder to Brunswick CSD Residents: The Governor's recent Executive Order extended the deadline for receiving mailed in ballots to Tuesday the 16th at 5PM. However, the order did not change the date of the election, so in-person collection of ballots ends at 5 PM today. Also, school districts may not distribute ballots to voters after 5 PM today.

Counting of ballots may begin Tuesday the 16th after 5 PM.
Please let us know if you have any questions or are facing any issues with the vote by contacting Catrina Schumaker at cschumaker@brunswickcsd.org!

Please reach out to us if you have any questions, or need further guidance. We are here for you every step of the way.

One way to do so is by understanding the causes and effects of stress and anxiety on your and your family, especially during this time surrounding COVID-19. Here we would like to share the following from the CDC, which details how stress can affect us, and what we can do to better cope: https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/daily-life-coping/managing-stress-anxiety.html

Finding the right career for you is a journey that requires thought, care, and perseverance! There are so many routes to choose from, and in our ever-evolving economy and society, it can be difficult to select a route that will be financially and personally rewarding.

With this in mind, we have provided two graphs of the Fastest Growing Jobs and the Most New Jobs that statisticians have determined over the past few years and leading into our future. We have also linked our resources below so you can learn more about these options, and what you could do to gain insight into potential career paths!

https://www.bls.gov/ooh/fastest-growing.htm
https://www.bls.gov/ooh/most-new-jobs.htm

On Wellness Wednesday and every day, it is important to take care of our health and the health of those around us! With this in mind, we would like to share the following message from the Capital District Tobacco-Free Communities group:

You may be aware of the concern that the youth vaping epidemic has put young people at greater risk of harm from COVID-19. Specifically, people who use tobacco products (including electronic cigarettes/vapes) may be more susceptible to COVID-19 and may suffer more severe health-related consequences. The health care community‚Äôs message to current smokers and vapers is clear: There is no better time to quit smoking/vaping than right now.

Attached (in the following district post) is a comprehensive list of recommended online resources for parents, students and teachers, including free smoking and vaping cessation resources, guidance to parents of youth who are addicted to nicotine, and educational resources for teachers.

https://www.brunswickcsd.org/news/resources-to-assist-in-response-to-covid-19-how-to-talk-to-your-child-about-smoking-e-vaping/

Happy Monday, Bengals!

Last week, we asked you to share how you are practicing thoughtfulness and kindness to those around you and to yourselves. Today, we would like to share the following picture of two of our students, Celia and Emme, who worked on letters to send to residents at the ARC of Rensselaer County.

We hope this brightens your day and jumpstarts your week on a positive note - and thank you, Celia and Emme, for sharing your thoughtfulness with us! We are #BengalProud to have such kind students ü•∞

Have a great week, Tamarac!
